<h2>New Venture</h2>

<%= form_for @venture do |f| %>
<%= f.label :title %>
<%= f.text_field :title %>
<%= f.label :description %>
<%= f.text_field :description %>
<p>Select your Industry</p>
<%= f.select(:category_id, @categories.map {|c| [c.title, c.id]}) %>
<p>Take some time to consider these questions before choosing your search terms, then check out our FAQs on how to choose good search terms.<br>
  Don't worry, you can change your search terms at any time.</p><br>
  <p>
    <ul>
      <li>What problems does your Venture solve?
      <li>What makes your Venture different or better than other Ventures?
      <li>What groups of people do you think would be interested in your Venture? Think of factors suck as age, gender, location, and financial capacity.
      <li>What are some similar companies or products? How would you search for these products online?
    </ul>
  </p>

<p>Add Notes:</p>
<%= f.text_area :notes %>
<%= f.label :notes %>
<%= f.submit "Next" %>

<% end  %>
